The evidence with the title 'Obama's economic record: an assessment | the New Yorker ' says Jan 9, 2017  ... At seven and ahalf years long , the Obama recovery now is one of the longest on record . In terms of annual G.D.P. growth, the rate of expansion has been relatively modest : since 2010, G.D.P. has risen by about 2.1 per cent a year. During the Bill Clinton recovery ( 1992 - 2000 ) , G.D.P.growthaveraged3.8 ... 
